				<td colspan="2"><span>Nice guide.  Something to add here though is use Kazumi's Note of Preservation if you are pulling mobs that are faster then you.  This song has saved me many times on certain pulls.  Also use jump to gain distance.  If you jump and run, you will move quicker then what you are pulling.  If you are pulling a mob like an anuek in rs, you might want to try to use snare to gain some distance.  I really don't use lull anymore even on old school stuff.  I prefer mez pulling.  Mez a mob pull what you get if its too much mez another then bring rest to group.  Have tank get on one and mez other.  Then you can either fade or have some fun by mezzing everything.  One thing to remember is not be playing any songs or have healer heal you til you fade.  You kinda need a good FT pool to use this technique too.
<br />

<br />
Conaden Darksong, 70 Bard
