				<td colspan="2"><span>Just one advanced tip.
<br />

<br />
Mobs who are aggroing you because they are assisting the mob you make mad, don't normally make assist calls themselves.
<br />

<br />
Basically, if you tag/aggro mob A, and mob B adds, Mob C will not generally aggro off mob B.
<br />

<br />
Why is this relevant? It keeps entire zones from landing on top of you on a bad pull.  It also lets you do some funky things with pulls.
<br />

<br />
Lets say you want to run thru a zone full of mobs, and drop your target at the zoneline, you can.  
<br />

<br />
Example: Deep in the zone are 3 mobs.  Your target, and 2 adds.  Step 1.  Lull possible add A.  Step 2.  Youre down to a basic split.  But instead of splitting, Mez add B.  Your target will assist off the mezed mob, and begin to chase you.  This is pretty normal.  Step 3.  Click/Cast invis and start high-tailing it to zone in.  You have one advantage that no other class has, you can run and cast.  Step 4. Pray.  Step 5. Pray some more, cause its crucial you time this right.  As soon as your intended target is past all the mobs that would have taken hours to clear.  Mez/snare (if possible) and pound fade.  Mob is stopped dead in its tracks for the next 12 secs, allowing you to reaggro, while a HUGE train of mobs is sitting slightly back from you wondering why they are there (they assisted the mob you mezed, which has worn off by now, and began the Train of Doom).  Step 6. Pull it the rest of the way and beat it into submission.
<br />

<br />
How often you will use this is minimal, but it gives you food for thought.
<br />

<br />
Rappa</span></td>
