				<td colspan="2"><span>Mitcheypoo, from above definately true, but fair warning to those attempting this, some mobs chase range is zone wide.
<br />

<br />
Got another tip.
<br />

<br />
Walking the Dog.  Basically using Mez (Wind based, not Sing) with a push component to position a mob where you want it.
<br />

<br />
Granted this is a pulling guide, so here's how I use it in such situations.
<br />

<br />
Sometimes you'll find yourself with 4-5 mobs sitting in a room that cant effectively be split or lulled.  No distance to break line of sight, etc makes it tough to get singles.  
<br />

<br />
Tag the mob you want with your Wind Based Mez (or your highest level to ensure a lock).  Everything aggros, and you immediately Fade.  A mezed mob doesn't make a assist call.  Use your wind mez to walk the mob back to you (or at least outside assist range).  Since bard mezes overwrite each other regardless of level, you can use your highest level mez to maintain solid control of it, and just pulse your push mezes to get the mob where you want it.  If you get resists, reapply best mez.
<br />

<br />
I remembered this from last nights Rathe Council Run, when i was primary mezzer (arg), and had to position the mobs.
<br />

<br />
Rappa</span></td>
